Available Tools: send_sms | send_bulk_sms | get_sms_status | get_sms_history
Call Schema: { "func_call": "string", "to": "string", "message": "string", "from": "string" }
Response Schema: { "message_id": "string", "to": "string", "status": "string", "cost": number, "timestamp": "string" }
---
Question: Transmit a booking confirmation to a traveler in Rome.
Call: { "func_call": "send_sms", "to": "+390612345678", "message": "Booking #RM8821 confirmed for Hotel Dante. Check-in after 3 PM.", "from": "TravelIT" }
Response: { "message_id": "msg_it_7739201", "to": "+390612345678", "status": "sent", "cost": 0.055, "timestamp": "2023-10-27T15:01:12Z" }

